cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper presents a novel keypoint detector for point clouds using deep learning techniques. The approach involves using saliency to determine the best candidates from point clouds and refining the point selection until the actual keypoints are obtained. This work is related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with detecting keypoints in point clouds. It is also related to robotics (cs.RO) as it can be used for robot perception and navigation. The use of deep learning techniques and neural networks makes it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it uses the term "saliency" which is a concept commonly used in NLP for identifying important words or phrases in text.
